idsecerit] ‘Id secerit' means all that Cicero has said, for this was not the first instance of a consul having been ordered to prison (Cic. De Legg. iii. 9). However, Halm observes, the consul did not reach the prison, for he was rescued by his friends and taken ,to Jupiter Stator's temple, as Appian says (B. C. ii. ll). Cicero leaves us to infer that he was taken to prison.
